Did you know that plant-based eating can alleviate demands of the food production system on the environment? Widespread adoption of plant-based diets could help to alleviate environmental issues such as climate change, land-system change, biodiversity loss, freshwater use, and nitrogen emissions.

_______________________________________________

By completing a short questionnaire, you can help Stanford researchers to better understand why people choose to adopt or not a plant-based dietary pattern.
 
If you are a social media user living in the US, aged 18 and above, you can learn more and respond to our online questionnaire using the link below.

You will have a chance to win a $75 gift card!

If you provide your contact information, you will be entered into a raffle to be conducted on September 1, 2021 (1 day after the survey is closed) for a $75 gift card. The drawing will be conducted by Dr. Matthew Landry in Palo Alto, California. Participation in the study is not required in order to participate in the raffle. You can enter the raffle if you do not start or complete the study task by contacting us via email. The chance of winning a prize is approximately 1 in 200. The winner will be notified immediately by email and provided with information on how to receive the prize.

For study-related questions, contact 1-408-493-0523. Participant's rights questions, contact 1-866-680-2906

By completing a short questionnaire, you can help Stanford researchers to better understand why people choose to adopt or not a plant-based dietary pattern.
 
If you are a social media user living in the US, aged 18 and above, you can learn more and respond to our online questionnaire using the link below.

You will have a chance to win a $75 gift card!

If you provide your contact information, you will be entered into a raffle to be conducted on September 1, 2021 (1 day after the survey is closed) for a $75 gift card. The drawing will be conducted by Dr. Matthew Landry in Palo Alto, California. Participation in the study is not required in order to participate in the raffle. You can enter the raffle if you do not start or complete the study task by contacting us via email. The chance of winning a prize is approximately 1 in 200. The winner will be notified immediately by email and provided with information on how to receive the prize.

For study-related questions, contact 1-408-493-0523. Participant's rights questions, contact 1-866-680-2906

data.ad_creative_body:
Please join us on this special day commemorating the 20th anniversary of the September 11, 2001, terrorist attacks. Pay tribute to those who gave the ultimate sacrifice in service to our country. Meet with fellow patriots and show your support for our military, police officers, and first responders.

Featured Speaker: Mayor Mike Murphy candidate for governor of Minnesota. Mike spent a number of years in law enforcement, small business and is Mayor of Lexington. Mike is an America First & Minnesota First Conservative.  

Guest Speakers & Candidates running for office:

Dennis Smith - Candidate for Attorney General

Phillip Parrish - Candidate for Secretary of State 

Kendall Qualls - Take Charge MN & Former candidate for Congress

Action 4 Liberty - Guest Speaker

More speakers TBD

MC’s 
TC Pearson & Bella Dangelo

Live DJ S-N-S Music playing patriotic music

Food and beverage served by Los Arcos Kitchen & Cantina 7386 Aiport View Drive SW, Rochester MN 55092

Family-Friendly Outdoor event, Bring a Chair, Patriotic Flags, Bathrooms On-Site, Lawn Games, and Patriotic Music.  

Meet the candidates from 1:00 pm - 2:00 pm 
Speakers and music from 2:00 pm - 5:00 pm

The premier children's museum in Kansas is coming to you! The Kansas Children's Discovery Mobile museum is packed with hands-on, educational play for all ages. Create art, build with real tools, explore technology, experience the power of air, run a pretend restaurant, practice engineering and more, with Discovery Center educators on-hand to engage the whole family in playful learning adventures! Mark your calendars and come on by!

September 25, 2021
10am - 2pm
455 SE Golf Park Blvd, Topeka, KS 66605

This is a free community event. Registration is not required. Sponsored by: Fellowship Hi-Crest, SENT Topeka, Childcare Aware.

Join Persia Nicole and B’more for Healthy Babies for "Purple Table Talk," A Virtual Townhall to celebrate Black Breastfeeding Week.  Learn more about the history of black breastfeeding in this country, tips from moms and doulas, and resources to help black women in Baltimore navigate the birthing and breastfeeding experience.

Learn more about B’more for Healthy Babies at www.healthybabiesbaltimore.com

Follow on IG: @bmore4healthybabies   
Follow on Twitter @bmoreforbabies
